'''''3D Tanx''''' is a [[shoot 'em up]] [[video game]] written by [[Don Priestley]] and published by [[DK'Tronics]] in 1982 for the [[ZX Spectrum]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseekid.cgi?id=0005140|title=3D Tanx|work=World of Spectrum}}</ref> [[Commodore 64]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lemon64.com/?game_id=3660|title=3D Tanx|work=Lemon64}}</ref> and [[BBC Micro]].

==Gameplay==
The aim of the game is to shoot [[tank]]s moving across a bridge, shown in the distance into the screen. The player aims a gun turret by adjusting its rotation and elevation, this being the '3D' aspect of the game. Skill and timing is required to strike the tanks.<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Sinclair User|issue=14|url=http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/014/softwre.htm|title=3D Tanx review|access-date=30 June 2007|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120913010446/http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/014/softwre.htm|archive-date=13 September 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

==Reception==
''[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]'' magazine wrote, "The graphics are very good and so is the sound," and concluded,"...and at the price, excellent value."<ref>{{cite journal|journal=CRASH|url=http://www.crashonline.org.uk/03/lguide13.htm|title=3D Tanx review|issue=3}}</ref>

